  "text": "where H x d is the number of 1-bits in the drug's fingerprint x d , and H x d ;x 0 d indicates the number of 1-bits common to fingerprints of two drug molecules x d and x 0 d under comparison. The above Tanimoto similarity measure is a valid PSD kernel function [CITATION_1] .",
